cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with a large-scale egocentric video benchmark, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques for object and action recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models and evaluation metrics, which are common in the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The dataset is recorded by participants in their native kitchen environments, which involves robotics and automation, making cs.RO (Robotics) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of anticipation models, which involves predicting future actions, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. Finally, the dataset includes videos, which involves multimedia analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category.
